{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T10:43:10.339Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Convolutions Are"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"convolution"},{"type":"text","text":" in a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) is a mathematical operation that applies a small, learnable filter (called a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"kernel"},{"type":"text","text":") across an input to detect local patterns. The kernel slides over the input data (like an image), performing element-wise multiplication at each position and summing the results to produce a single output value. This creates a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"feature map"},{"type":"text","text":" that highlights where specific patterns (e.g., edges, textures) occur. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Convolutions Matter in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convolutions are the foundational building block of CNNs, which are core architectures in generative AI for:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Application"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Role"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Image generation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CNNs (e.g., in GANs) generate realistic images by learning spatial hierarchies "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Computer vision"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Detect objects, faces, and patterns with superior accuracy "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Spatial data analysis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Process any data with spatial structure (images, video, grids)"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CNNs achieve "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"translational invariance"},{"type":"text","text":"—the same kernel detects a feature regardless of where it appears in the input. This is critical because a cat two pixels left is still a cat."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Convolutions Work (Core Mechanics)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step-by-step process:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Kernel initialization"},{"type":"text","text":": A small matrix (e.g., 3×3 or 5×5) with random weights is created"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sliding"},{"type":"text","text":": The kernel moves across the input with a defined "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"stride"},{"type":"text","text":" (step size)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Element-wise multiplication"},{"type":"text","text":": At each position, multiply kernel values by overlapping input values"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Summation"},{"type":"text","text":": Add all products to get one output pixel"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Repeat"},{"type":"text","text":": Continue until the kernel covers the entire input"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key parameters:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parameter"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it controls"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Effect"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Kernel size"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Filter dimensions (e.g., 3×3)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Smaller = local patterns; larger = global patterns"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stride"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step size between positions"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Larger stride = smaller output"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Padding"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Extra values around input border"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Preserves input size; prevents edge information loss"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits of Convolutions"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parameter efficiency"},{"type":"text","text":": Fewer parameters than fully connected networks (kernels share weights across space) "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local connectivity"},{"type":"text","text":": Detects local patterns (edges, textures) rather than global correlations"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"GPU parallelization"},{"type":"text","text":": Convolutions are easy to parallelize across GPU cores "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hierarchical feature learning"},{"type":"text","text":": Early layers detect edges; deeper layers detect complex shapes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs & Limitations"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Limitation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explanation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fixed spatial range"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standard convolutions only see local regions; may miss long-range dependencies"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Grid distortion"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can struggle with non-grid data (graphs, irregular meshes)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Computational cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deep CNNs with many layers can be expensive to train "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Solutions"},{"type":"text","text":": Dilated convolutions expand the receptive field without increasing weights; separable convolutions reduce computation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of a convolution as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"stamp"},{"type":"text","text":" moving across a document:\n- The stamp (kernel) has a pattern carved into it\n- As it slides, it highlights where that pattern matches\n- Multiple stamps (different kernels) detect different features simultaneously\n- The network learns which patterns are useful through training"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convolutions apply learnable filters to detect local patterns like edges and textures"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"They enforce "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"local connectivity"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"translational invariance"},{"type":"text","text":", critical for image data"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CNNs are computationally efficient due to weight sharing and GPU parallelization "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In generative AI, CNNs form the backbone of architectures like GANs for image generation "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Parameters (kernel size, stride, padding) control what and how features are extracted"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Convolutions remain the dominant operation in vision-based generative models, though newer architectures (e.g., Vision Transformers) are emerging for tasks requiring long-range context. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://d2l.ai/chapter_convolutional-neural-networks/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"d2l"}]}]}}
